# Testing with GOV.UK Wallet's Verifier Integration (Sandbox) environment

When you are developing your verification process, you must confirm that you are able to [receive credential information](/consuming-and-verifying-credentials) from a GOV.UK Wallet holders device.  You should use GOV.UK Wallet's Verifier Integration (Sandbox) tools to support this.

The sandbox will allow you to create a sample credential, and save it to a test GOV.UK Wallet instance.  You can then present the credential to your verification process, and confirm you are able to receive a verifiable credential.  You will be able to complete this flow on both Android and iOS devices.

The sandbox tools are for specific testing and development purposes, and must not be used as part of a live integration with GOV.UK Wallet.  Since each verification process is different, the sandbox is limited to testing the Verifiable Presentation of a credential.

Your verification process will depend on the types of credentials you will accept, and the credential information you request.  To ensure this meets your requirements you should:

- understand the credential types you wish to use
- confirm the credential information you wish to use for each credential type
- implement testing of your verification requirements, without using the sandbox tools

